Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.96,0:00:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So\Nhere
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.43,0:01:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,heaven\NGloria and excelsius.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.56,0:01:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So operating the body this morning is a\Nbit of a problem. You just have to be
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.04,0:01:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,patient.\NSometimes the condition is stronger than
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.11,0:01:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,others and uh\Nyou'll have to put up whatever is today.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.43,0:01:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people are new today?\NUhhuh. All right. Mhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.64,0:01:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very easy to see\Nthat everything is happening
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.68,0:01:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,spontaneously\Nthat even your thinkingness is happening
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.96,0:02:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,all of its own\Nand you you think that you're deciding
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.00,0:02:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,what you're going to think but you're\Nnot.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.71,0:02:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So you get detached from your own\Nthinking is the same as the world. You
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.68,0:02:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,see the world around you is moving\Nwithout your help. I'm right. All these
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.20,0:02:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,people are are managing to survive\Nwithout you helping them to be here and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.72,0:02:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,move and talk.\NAnd so what you do is you get detached
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.44,0:02:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and you begin to become the witness.\NUm to become the witness is not a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.04,0:02:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,difficult step. It's only a matter of\Nletting go the narcissistic
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.36,0:02:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,self-indulgence of the thinking of of\Nthat there's an eye causing things.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.04,0:02:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is causing anything.\NThere no causes in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.20,0:02:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only consequences.\NAnd so what you do is you let go
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.16,0:03:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,identifying with the linear. And you\Nrealize that your reality is nonlinear,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.16,0:03:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is witnessing. And then\Nbehind that which is witnessing, that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.51,0:03:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,which is aware that you're witnessing.\NAnd already you've removed yourself from
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.08,0:03:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,out there and individual personal eye\Nand the guilt and anxiety of cause being
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.15,0:03:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the cause of all that happens. And\Nyou've moved into this the condition of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.20,0:03:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,humility.\NWith profound humility, you will see
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.64,0:03:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're not the cause of anything,\Nwhich is welcome news because that means
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.84,0:03:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you're also not guilty of anything.\Nsomething happens. You say, "I don't
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.64,0:03:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,know. The mind did it.\NThe mind did it." That's what I can't
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.51,0:03:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,help it. The mind did it. up\Nto become the witness. Then you become
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.15,0:04:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,aware\Nthen of the spontaneity of evolution and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.36,0:04:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to witness all phenomena are\Nthe
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.12,0:04:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution of creation.\NCreation has a source but no cause. It
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.76,0:04:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,has no beginning and it has no end.\NYou witness the unfoldment the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.56,0:04:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,unfoldment of creation. Yeah,\Nthere is no problem with about creation
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.19,0:04:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's what you're witnessing.\NU
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.08,0:04:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the fact that it's all happening\Nspontaneously is not difficult to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.91,0:04:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not difficult to move from the\Nparticipant subject out there the linear
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.96,0:04:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and move into being the field out of\Nwhich the phenomena you're being aware
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.08,0:04:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of the phenomena\Nthat that which you are is the field and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.24,0:05:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,not the content of the field.\NThis observation escapes about 99% of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.60,0:05:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind.\NLet's see if that was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.32,0:05:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,99%'s correct. Yes. And at least 99%\Nof humanity is completely unaware of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.44,0:05:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,what we're talking about this morning.\NAnd we're not counting on widespread
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.56,0:05:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,acceptance.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.72,0:05:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that you are the context rather than the\Ncontent.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.88,0:05:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You are that\Nfrom which awareness radiates and out of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.96,0:05:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,which consciousness arises. The source\Nis consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.84,0:05:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The light of God is consciousness.\NThe light of God is your own
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.88,0:05:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness.\NAnd as you let go of misidentifying with
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.28,0:06:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that which you are not, it becomes\Nstunningly apparent.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.16,0:06:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,At which point you retire\Nand they call the doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.91,0:06:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He's lost his wits.\NThat's true. You do lose your wits and
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.44,0:06:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes it's worse than others. So\Ntoday I am witness and you'll have to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.60,0:06:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,put up with that condition.\NAll right. We always have some new
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.31,0:06:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,people. So we do some review of some\Nvery basic things. Then we move. Do you
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.91,0:06:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,want to start with what's new first and\Nthen move back to what you know or you
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.68,0:06:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,want to start with what you know to move\Nto what's new?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.88,0:06:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,>> All the new people. You want what's new?\N>> Start with what's new. Then move to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.24,0:07:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,what's\N>> we'll do both.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.03,0:07:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Beginnings and ends are all in your\Nhead. They're in the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.44,0:07:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We do start just for orientation with\Nthe calibrated map of consciousness as a
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.40,0:07:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,common point of reference.\NYeah, friend. And so um that's what
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.12,0:07:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll do. Start with that one.\NAnd well, yes, explain it. I'll explain
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.19,0:07:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,it maybe a little bit differently.\NWhere's uh the first slide there?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.19,0:07:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's There we go. What do you know?\NUm
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.12,0:07:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll reexlain the map of consciousness.\NI'm sorry I went from one to a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.19,0:07:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You should have gone from A to Z\Nbecause everybody thinks a number, a
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.96,0:07:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,higher number makes you better than\Nother people.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.63,0:08:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it doesn't. It just means you're\Nseeing things in a different light.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.24,0:08:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Blue, green. We could do it with colors.\NAnd I've decided the best way to do it
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.03,0:08:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is with money.\NSo, this calibration here is not worth
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.36,0:08:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,much money.\NAnd that's worth $1,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.72,0:08:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we're all trying for the jackpot.\NSo the lower levels of consciousness are
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.76,0:08:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,just not worth much. They\Nthey'll only get you a few bomb loads of
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.64,0:08:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,kids to blow up or something like that.\NNothing spectacular. You know what I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.88,0:08:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,saying?\NAll right. So we we decided we we change
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.12,0:09:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it to money. And uh these are not worth\Nmuch money down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.60,0:09:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh\Nthe exchange rate depends on the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.44,0:09:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,exchange rate. The media have jacked up\Nthe exchange rate which we'll get into
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.12,0:09:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,later. So so that this now pays more\Nthan this up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.88,0:09:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh god, it's hysterical.\NI don't know how the world survives and
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.16,0:09:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,uh God tells me not to\Nuh let on. So I quote, "Do you ever hear
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.08,0:09:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,preachers, God tells them this and God\Ntells them that?" I'd listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.68,0:09:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,All I hear is silence.\NThe sound of God is silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.39,0:09:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a thousand.\NCalibrates at a thousand. The sound of
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.76,0:10:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,God is silence.\NTo have sound you have to have
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.08,0:10:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,linearity. You have to have that which\Nis sound and that which is not sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.36,0:10:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you have to give configuration to\Nthe sound. Therefore mantras and things
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.68,0:10:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and going and things will take you to a\Ncertain level and beyond that you get
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.68,0:10:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you become aware of the silence behind\Nthe sound. And so this purpose of the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.56,0:10:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,sound is to take you to the silence.\NThat's why repeating a mantra repeatedly
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.83,0:10:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,can sometimes really just lead to an\Naltered state of consciousness and the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.83,0:10:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,high feeling that you get disappears\Nwhen you stop the mantra. So they all
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.24,0:10:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,have limited limited\Nuh usages.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.12,0:10:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,There is cysts at certain points but you\Ncan't put your whole life uh as a
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.16,0:10:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,mantra. You can put your whole life as\Nas a prayer because a prayer is a
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.68,0:11:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,verbalization of a nonlinear\Nintentionality
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.00,0:11:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,of prayer to make your life a prayer to\Nbecome that to become that and that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.51,0:11:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,which you are speaks louder than what\Nyou say. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.60,0:11:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Essence speaks louder than perception\Nwhich we'll get to later. All right. So
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.88,0:11:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the u the levels of\Nconsciousness. As I said, we it's
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.76,0:11:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,relatively well known. It was an\Narbitrary scale
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.24,0:11:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,uh because we needed some way to refer\Nto it. It's also logarithmic. So that as
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.88,0:11:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you as you go up, the numbers increase\Nvery very rapidly. That's why we use
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.48,0:11:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,logarithms\Nvery very rapidly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.32,0:11:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Now, what did I say was the\Nnext uh slide after that? Any questions
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.64,0:11:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,on the calibrated level of\Nconsciousness?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.51,0:11:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,As I say, it doesn't say that you're\Nbetter than others. It's not a matter of
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.72,0:11:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,better because our status oriented uh\Nyou know society we say it's better.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.76,0:12:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not better. It's different than\Ndifferent then. And very often to be in
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.36,0:12:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in a different than state of\Nconsciousness that is not appropriate to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.68,0:12:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,where you are, it can be a hindrance.\NYou understand? to be um blissed out,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.60,0:12:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, when you're driving is not so\Ngreat,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.76,0:12:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to pull over. So, you have to\Nsort of be in what's appropriate. Uh but
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.88,0:12:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that begins to adjust itself\Nautomatically. But it is true that if
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.56,0:12:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,you suddenly advance to a high state,\Nyou may be quite incapacitated. So it's
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.95,0:12:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,well to have spiritual friends hang out\Nwith spiritual people spiritual friends
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.83,0:12:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and you let them know that you're you\Nknow seriously in studying etc. And if
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.68,0:12:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,you go into such states they will\Nrecognize what it is. Uhhuh. And that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.12,0:12:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,was a function I used to have for the\NZen monastery back east. I was a
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.04,0:13:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,consultant to the Episcopal Dasis, uh\Nthe Catholic Dasis, the ministerial
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.12,0:13:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,council, the Zen monastery\Nand they would bring in people and is he
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.39,0:13:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,catatonic or is he in samati they didn't\Nknow
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.48,0:13:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and um because they would go into a\Nsilent still state which is not
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.60,0:13:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,dissimilar from catatonia which I was\Nused to see in the hospital you know I
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.39,0:13:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,think I told you that story I had a\Ncatatonic that hadn't spoken in 20
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.60,0:13:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,years. And they would put his hand up\Nlike this and he would stay that way
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.76,0:13:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,year in and year out, not move. He would\Nhave to move his hand down like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.32,0:13:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And one time he saw the head of the\Nhospital coming. And the nurses weren't
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.88,0:13:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,supposed to smoke or drink coffee in the\Noffice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.07,0:13:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And uh he saw them. He hadn't spoken in\N20 years. All of a sudden, he turned and
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.04,0:13:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,he said, "Travis,\Nthe nurses put their coffee in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.80,0:14:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the only thing he ever said.\NTravis is coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.72,0:14:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Unbelievable. They had the t they had\Nthe tube feed him and he wouldn't eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.48,0:14:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, catatonia. So in a high bliss\Nstate, it might be difficult to tell is
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.95,0:14:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,this person catatonic\Nor in a high state of bliss and without
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.12,0:14:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrating them you can't tell. So the\Nvalue of this discovery of course the my
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.60,0:14:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,interest was in sharing it with the\Nworld and u
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.95,0:14:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,you know why I teach is the same reason\NFleming
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.95,0:14:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,ran around after he discovered\Npenicellin you know he discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.39,0:14:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,penicellin accidentally just as I\Ndiscovered uh the basis of how we
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.51,0:14:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,discern truth from falsehood was a\Nchance observation which I got in an
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.48,0:14:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,instant what it signified\NAnd Fleming discovered the same thing
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.95,0:14:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,with the petri dish when he noticed that\Nuh the moles had killed off the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.76,0:15:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,bacteria. Oh my god, he he got what it\Nmeant. You see, it's one thing to see
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.48,0:15:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,it, it's another to get what it means.\NAnd Fleming got what it meant. Oh my
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.04,0:15:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,god, he got what it meant. Then by\Nexperimentation,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.56,0:15:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,he discovered penicellin. And of course,\Nit's a whole new era. Those amongst us
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.63,0:15:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,who are doctors remember\Nthe days when everybody had was dying of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.12,0:15:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,typhoid and malaria and polio and\Ntuberculosis and and all the terrible
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.80,0:15:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,diseases which no longer even exist. You\Ndon't even see see these illnesses
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.12,0:15:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,anymore.\NSo it's transformed the world
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.32,0:15:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,antibiotics and uh so what Fleming was\Ninterested in was the importance of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.27,0:15:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,discovery and he couldn't get anybody to\Nlisten to it because it was coming from
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.63,0:15:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,a different context\Nand he ran around for some five years.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.88,0:15:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody would listen to him. Then in\NWorld War II the uh the combatants of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.88,0:15:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,course had injuries. This soldiers and\Nsailors
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.04,0:15:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,had injuries. So\Nwound injury, the infections, the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.68,0:16:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,infection was what finally killed you.\NThe infection was the main thing. You
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.92,0:16:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,got a bullet through the arm. That was I\Nwouldn't say it's nothing because I've
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.92,0:16:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,had similar things in there. Not\Nnothing. But uh what killed you then was
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.00,0:16:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the bacterial infection. Six weeks\Nlater, he had six weaver six weeks of
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.04,0:16:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,high fever and various things. So\Nwhat uh Fleming's motivation was to to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.16,0:16:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,share this with the world and it was\Nonly because of the military's need in
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.39,0:16:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,World War II that some of the military\Nthe army finally listened to him and we
